<div style="float:left; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#97CBFF; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>I mean, some of the &quot;big shots&quot; are what you would commonly call &quot;reality benders&quot;</p>
<p>But what are the chances of people happen to be reality benders, and just happen to be invested in art, and just happen to want to use their ability in that field above all else?</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: left;"></div>
<div style="float:right; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#A6FFA6; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>Well, when you put it that way&#8230;</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: right;"></div>
<div style="float:left; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#97CBFF; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>I think it's just that bunch of people who got really famous, hence the misconception :P</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: left;"></div>
<div style="float:right; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#A6FFA6; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>Ummm.</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: right;"></div>
<div style="float:left; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#97CBFF; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>I don't really like it that way, but some people do that well, I guess?</p>
<p>Then again, from how I see it, simply using reality bending on art kinda defeat the purpose of anart?<br />
It's almost like slapping summoning circles on machines to create paratech instead of using a scientific mind to analyze magic :P</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: left;"></div>
<div style="float:right; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#A6FFA6; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>Then how do you actually do anart?</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: right;"></div>
<div style="float:left; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#97CBFF; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>Um, it's kinda difficult to say?</p>
<p>For me anart is like, creating art strong enough, that the sheer idea and emotion can stir reality?<br />
To actually bring your piece to life?</p>
<p>It's not like using magic or reality bending and apply them to art, the piece's paranormal aspect manifest the moment the idea comes through.</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: left;"></div>
<div style="float:right; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#A6FFA6; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>If you're really using your idea to shape reality, isn't that reality bending?</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: right;"></div>
<div style="float:left; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#97CBFF; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>Um, let me put it this way<br />
I can affect reality, but only through art? And technically everyone can do that, it's just very difficult</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: left;"></div>
<div style="float:right; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#A6FFA6; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>Are you saying that it's the art that twists reality, not you?</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: right;"></div>
<div style="float:left; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#97CBFF; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>Um not quite</p>
<p>Have you heard like the concept of &quot;flow&quot;?</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: left;"></div>
<div style="float:right; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#A6FFA6; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>I'm not sure.</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: right;"></div>
<div style="float:left; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#97CBFF; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>From what I know, a lot of anartist channel this, &quot;flow&quot; thing when they work<br />
Some aware, some just unconciously, and there's different names to it, but it's like a kind of feeling, like everything fits into the perfect slot, and you know if you go down with that feeling, that flow you feel, idea will be molded into art, and the art will manifest into something beautiful</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: left;"></div>
<div style="float:right; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#A6FFA6; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>That actually sounds kind of like how some magic works.</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: right;"></div>
<div style="float:left; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#97CBFF; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>Maybe? But it's not like just applying magic to art, it's more of, a different system?</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: left;"></div>
<div style="float:right; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#A6FFA6; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>No no, I get that.</p>
<p>So is there entry requirements? It is like only specific people can channel that?</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: right;"></div>
<div style="float:left; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#97CBFF; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>Well&#8230;<br />
I mean, technically we can all access that<br />
It's just that<br />
Ugh.</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: left;"></div>
<div style="float:right; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#A6FFA6; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>Um, did I say something wrong?</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: right;"></div>
<div style="float:left; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#97CBFF; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>Oh no no, I was reminded of something a friend of mine did ._.</p>
<p>It didn't turn out very well for her</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: left;"></div>
<div style="float:right; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#A6FFA6; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>I'm sorry.</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: right;"></div>
<div style="float:left; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#97CBFF; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>You know, what the hell, I should talk about it</p>
<p>A while back my friend tried to pass out this small thing she wrote designed to condition people's mind to be able to acess the flow<br />
Not really the altering your mind type, but more like, open doors for you to see this is possible?</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: left;"></div>
<div style="float:right; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#A6FFA6; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>Got it.</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: right;"></div>
<div style="float:left; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#97CBFF; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>And most of the people who read that ended up creating anart of their own</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: left;"></div>
<div style="float:right; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#A6FFA6; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>Wow.</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: right;"></div>
<div style="float:left; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#97CBFF; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>Yeah<br />
It was pretty amazing, but of course, attracted too much attention</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: left;"></div>
<div style="float:right; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#A6FFA6; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>Oh. I'm really sorry.</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: right;"></div>
<div style="float:left; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#97CBFF; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>No it's okay, she's just retired from the anartist circle for good. Sane and well.</p>
<p>Let's not dwell on that topic though.</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: left;"></div>
<div style="float:right; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#A6FFA6; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>Of course.<br />
I mean, this certainly changes things. To think that even ordinary people can affect reality in this way.</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: right;"></div>
<div style="float:left; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#97CBFF; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>How about I introduce you to a few more anartists, and you ask around?<br />
Won't be &quot;snake people&quot; this time, of course :P</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: left;"></div>
<div style="float:right; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#A6FFA6; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>That would be great.</p>
<p>Let's meet at my boss's place.</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: right;"></div>
<div style="float:left; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#97CBFF; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>How about next Wednesday, afternoon?</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: left;"></div>
<div style="float:right; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#A6FFA6; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>Sounds good to me.</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: right;"></div>
<div style="float:left; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#97CBFF; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>Cool, see you there then :3</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: left;"></div>
<div style="float:right; width: 500px; text-align: right;">
<div style="font-size: 10pt; background:#A6FFA6; text-align: left; padding: 1px 20px;">
<p>Looking forward to it.</p>
</div>
<br />
<br /></div>
<div style="clear: right;"></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
